Pleased to have joined my fellow colleagues to reaffirm our support for D.C. Statehood. 

DC has a larger population than two states. Yet, these citizens do not have a vote in Congress. Today, the House passed H.R. 51 to end this injustice & bring DC residents one step closer to the representation they deserve. #DCStatehood

As House Speaker, it is my official privilege to join my G7 colleagues in the United Kingdom for this year’s Speakers’ Meeting.

President Lincoln once cautioned the country of “the silent artillery of time,” threatening to erode our memories. Let us renew our vow: that time shall not dim the memory of our heroes.

As Americans across the country mark September 11, we recommit to our sacred promise to never forget – both what we lost and the unity and strength that we found.

It was a solemn privilege to visit the @911memorial to mark 20 years since the terror attacks on our nation.
 
When we talk about #September11 we tread on sacred ground. Let us continue to hold dear the memories of those we lost and honor those who rose to heroism that day.

node.text:
Twenty years later, after the rubble has been cleared, the fires extinguished and our cities rebuilt, Americans come together today to reaffirm our sacred pledge to #NeverForget911. 
 
We still hold dear the memories of the 3,000 beautiful souls who perished in the attacks, and we pray for their families. We also remember the extraordinary unity, hope and heroism of that day, from the courageous first responders to the everyday Americans who stepped up to answer our nation’s call. And we remain inspired by their spirit of service and sacrifice as we continue our work to build a more peaceful future for generations to come.   

Read my full statement on twenty years since the September 11th attacks here. https://www.speaker.gov/newsroom/91121

My advice to young women leaders is this:

Know your power.
Know your why.
Know your vision.

This country needs you, and there is no contribution that anyone can make that is like yours.

Honored to receive an honorary degree and share this advice in a Presidential Colloquium as part of @SmithCollege’s Year on Democracies.

node.text: Proud to join Congressman John B. Larson and Governor Ned Lamont yesterday at Goodwin University to celebrate the expanded Biden Child Tax Credit. Next week, American families will receive their third check from this life-changing tax cut. The Child Tax Credit is a recognition of how we value children, how we support families and how we must honor President Biden's transformative vision to Build Back Better, starting with women.

node.text:
This week, the House passed H.R. 4, the John R. Lewis Voting Rights Advancement Act to combat the assault on democracy across America by restoring the power of the Voting Rights Act.
 
The late John Lewis, often referred to as the conscience of the Congress, said the vote is “the most powerful non-violent tool we have in a democracy.” In America, the right to vote must never, ever be compromised. 
 
Congresswoman Terri Sewell’s district is full of history, but she is making progress in addition to honoring that history. Proud to stand with her and House Democrats in fighting #ForThePeople.
